    "name": "Creating Custom Components",
    "content": [
        {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Docusaurus brings the full power of React, so it's very straightforward to install and use new components via `npm` or create something on-the-fly.\n\nTo create one, first create a new file in [[sym:./src/components(2fe8976c-9527-40da-87eb-b0a6d47a4393)]] named after your component along with whatever style customizations it will use. A great example of this is in [[sym:./src/components/SocialAccounts.js(658eea15-34fb-493c-8f22-8fd250564693)]] with the corresponding styles in [[sym:./src/components/SocialAccounts.module.css(7cf49bca-57b4-4454-a352-de7fabf4e8fd)]]"
        },
        {
            "type": "snippet",
            "lines": [
                "*import React from 'react';",
