                "*    return (",
                "*        <section className={styles.socialCard}>",
                "*            <div className=\"container\">",
                "*                <div className=\"row\">",
                "*                    {SocialList.map((props, idx) => (",
                "*                        <SocialCard key={idx} {...props} />",
                "*                    ))}",
                "*                </div>",
                "*            </div>",
                "*        </section>",
                "*    );",
                "*}"
            ],
            "firstLineNumber": 89,
            "path": "src/components/SocialAccounts.js",
            "comments": [
                "Then export whatever you want to make available, just make sure you have a default and (only) one of them is exported as such."
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "snippet",
            "lines": [
                "*.socialCard {",
                "*    display: flex;",
                "*    align-items: center;",
                "*    padding: 2rem 0;",
                "*    width: 100%;",
                "*}"
            ],
            "firstLineNumber": 1,
            "path": "src/components/SocialAccounts.module.css",
            "comments": [
                "Because not every component is loaded on every page, there's no reason to always have their styles loaded in the global scope. Additionally, even if we are using a plugin somewhere that renders on every page load (e.g. in the footer), that doesn't mean we'll always be using it. If we disable it, then any styles associated with it become useless overhead.\n\nFinally, if we ever want to package the component separately, it's ideal to package the styles in a self-contained way.\n\nIf you're writing a component and the urge to stick something in [[sym:./src/css/custom.css(f5a62a7b-edb6-43cb-82a3-eb927779551a)]] sneaks in, there's a really good chance you're not writing a mere component anymore."
            ]
        }
